The article discusses the significance of appointing federal judges and highlights the achievement of confirming 150 life-tenured federal judges since the author took office. These judges play a crucial role in various aspects of society, such as ensuring fair trials, protecting fundamental rights, and overseeing worker safety. The judges come from diverse professional backgrounds, including labor and immigration attorneys, public defenders, and civil rights lawyers. The author emphasizes the qualifications, commitment to the rule of law, and dedication to the Constitution of these judges. Furthermore, the author expresses gratitude to the political leaders who have worked together to accomplish this milestone and emphasizes the ongoing commitment to filling judicial vacancies with highly qualified and impartial appointees.